        <heading>2369.8.  Right to partition; no exclusion by agreement; judicial partition</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2369.8.  Right to partition; no exclusion by agreement; judicial partition
A spouse has the right to demand partition of former community property at any time.  A contrary agreement is absolutely null.
If the spouses are unable to agree on the partition, either spouse may demand judicial partition which shall be conducted in accordance with R.S. 9:2801.</p>
        </content>
